Adagrad/¶

For a single variable linear regression ML model, build a function to find the optimum Theta_0 and Theta_1 parameters using Adagrad optimization algorithm.¶

The funtion should have the following input parameters:¶

1. Input data as a matrix (or vector based on your data).¶
2. Target label as a vector.¶
3. Learning rate.¶
4. Epsilon.¶
5. Maximum number of iterations (Epochs).¶

The funtion should return the following outputs:¶

1. All predicted Theta_0 in all iterations.¶
2. All predicted Theta_1 in all iterations.¶
3. Corresponding loss for each Theta_0 and Theta_1 predictions.¶
4.All hypothesis outputs (prdicted labels) for each Theta_0 and Theta_1 predictions.¶
5.Final Optimum values of Theta_0 and Theta_1.¶

Choose the suitable number of iterations, learning rate, Epsilon, and stop criteria.¶

Calculate r2 score. Shouldn't below 0.9¶

Plot the required curves (loss-epochs, loss-theta0, loss-theta1, all fitted lines per epoch (single graph), best fit line)¶

Try different values of the huperparameters and see the differnce in your results.¶

def Adagrad(x,y,alpha,epochs):
    theta_0=[]
    theta_1=[]
    ress=[]
    theta0=0
    theta1=0
    hyp=[]
    v0=0
    v1=0
    v_0=[] 
    v_1=[]

 

    for i in range(epochs):
        h=theta0+theta1*x
        hyp.append(h)
        error = sum((h-y)**2)
        res = error/ (2 * len(x))
        ress.append(res)
        a = sum(h-y) / ( len(x))
        b = sum((h-y)*x) / ( len(x))
        
        v0=v0+ (a**2)
        v_0.append(v0)
        
        theta0 = theta0 - (alpha/(v0**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*a
        theta_0.append(theta0)
        
        v1=v1+ (b**2)
        v_1.append(v1)
        
        theta1 = theta1 - (alpha/(v1**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*b
        theta_1.append(theta1)
        
    dict1={"theta_0":theta0,"theta_1":theta1,"losses":ress,"hypothesis output":hyp,"optimum theta_0":theta_0,"optimum theta_1":theta_1}
    return dict1

def RMSProp(x,y,alpha,beta,epochs):
    theta_0=[]
    theta_1=[]
    ress=[]
    theta0=0
    theta1=0
    hyp=[]
    v0=0
    v1=0
    v_0=[] 
    v_1=[]
    beta

    for i in range(epochs):
        h=theta0+theta1*x
        hyp.append(h)
        error = sum((h-y)**2)
        res = error/ (2 * len(x))
        ress.append(res)
        a = sum(h-y) / ( len(x))
        b = sum((h-y)*x) / ( len(x))
        
        
        v0=((beta*v0)+ ((1-beta)*(a**2)))
        v_0.append(v0)
        
        theta0 = theta0 - (alpha/(v0**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*a
        theta_0.append(theta0)
        
        v1=beta*v1+ ((1-beta)*(b**2))
        v_1.append(v1)
        
        theta1 = theta1 - (alpha/(v1**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*b
        theta_1.append(theta1)
        
        
    dict1={"theta_0":theta0,"theta_1":theta1,"losses":ress,"hypothesis output":hyp,"optimum theta_0":theta_0,"optimum theta_1":theta_1}
    return dict1

def Adam(x,y,alpha,beta,epochs):
    theta_0=[]
    theta_1=[]
    ress=[]
    theta0=0
    theta1=0
    hyp=[]
    v0=0
    v1=0
    v_0=[] 
    v_1=[]
    m0=0
    m1=0
    m_0=[]
    m_1=[]

    for i in range(epochs):
        h=theta0+theta1*x
        hyp.append(h)
        error = sum((h-y)**2)
        res = error/ (2 * len(x))
        ress.append(res)
        a = sum(h-y) / ( len(x))
        b = sum((h-y)*x) / ( len(x))
        
        m0=((beta*m0)+ ((1-beta)*(a)))
        m_0.append(m0)
        
        v0=((beta*v0)+ ((1-beta)*(a**2)))
        v_0.append(v0)
        
        theta0 = theta0 - (alpha/(v0**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*m0
        theta_0.append(theta0)
        
        m1=((beta*m1)+ ((1-beta)*(a)))
        m_1.append(m1)
        
        v1=beta*v1+ ((1-beta)*(b**2))
        v_1.append(v1)
        
        theta1 = theta1 - (alpha/(v1**(1/2))+(sys.float_info.epsilon))*m1
        theta_1.append(theta1)
        
        
    dict1={"theta_0":theta0,"theta_1":theta1,"losses":ress,"hypothesis output":hyp,"optimum theta_0":theta_0,"optimum theta_1":theta_1,"m0":m0,"m1":m1,"m_0":m_0,"m_1":m_1}
    return dict1
